cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on generating task-specific attention maps for weakly supervised localization tasks on image datasets such as MS COCO, PASCAL VOC07, and ImageNet. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new backpropagation scheme for top-down attention in CNN classifiers. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper introduces the concept of contrastive attention to make the top-down attention maps more discriminative. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category as the paper briefly mentions the usefulness of their method in the text-to-region association task on the Flickr30k Entities dataset. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a less likely category as the paper focuses on the neural attention of a CNN classifier rather than evolutionary computing.
